This value may be a name or IP address of another CallButler server, or a SIP URI.

data.name: lblSTUN.HelpText
data.value: STUN enables CallButler to determine your public IP address if you are behind a NAT enabled router or firewall. In most cases you should leave this turned on, but you may try turning this off if you have trouble connecting to or hearing CallButler when you make a call.

data.name: smoothLabel14.HelpText
data.value: This value specifies the number of concurrent calls that CallButler can handle at one time.

data.name: smoothLabel9.HelpText
data.value: This is the network port CallButler will use to communicate with your VoIP provider. In most cases this should be set to 5060, but it can be changed if you run into network or firewall conflicts.

data.name: smoothLabel10.HelpText
data.value: If this is left blank, CallButler will use a default STUN server. If you would like to specify your own STUN server, you may do it here.

data.name: smoothLabel16.HelpText
data.value: If this is turned on, CallButler will automatically send any error messages to the Email addres you provide below.

data.name: smoothLabel16.Text
data.value: Send me an Email when errors occur

data.name: lblErrors.HelpText
data.value:
If this is turned on, CallButler will automatically send error reports to Telephony2.
Leaving this on will greatly help us in debugging any problems that you may encounter and enable us to improve overall product quality.

data.name: lblErrors.Text
data.value: Automatically report and send server errors to Telephony2

data.name: smoothLabel12.HelpText
data.value:
Specify how much logging information CallButler should collect and store.
Errors only - Only log errors when they occur.
Basic information - Log basic information like who called and when they called.
Detailed information - Log extremely detailed information about the call including what happend during the call.

data.name: smoothLabel11.HelpText
data.value:
Specify where CallButler will store logging information.
Do not store logs - CallButler will not store any logging information.
Store logs in text files - CallButler will write logging information to a series of text files on the hard drive.
Store logs in Windows system event log - CallButler will store logging information in the Windows Event Log.

data.name: cboLogStorage.Items2
data.value: Store logs in Windows system event log

data.name: smoothLabel8.HelpText
data.value: This is volume that Text-To-Speech greetings will be played at. Specifying too high of a value here can result in distortion and make your greetings harder to understand.

data.name: smoothLabel7.HelpText
data.value: This is volume that voicemails will be recorded at.

data.name: smoothLabel6.HelpText
data.value: This is volume that sound based greetings and hold music will be played at. Specifying too high of a value here can result in distortion and make your greetings harder to understand.

data.name: smoothLabel5.HelpText
data.value: When CallButler uses Text-To-Speech to speak a greeting it will use the voice defined here unless otherwise specified by the greeting itself.

data.name: lblSSL.HelpText
data.value: Check this if your SMTP server requires SSL encryption to connect. In most cases this will not be selected, but some newer SMTP servers may require this.

data.name: smoothLabel4.HelpText
data.value: Specify your password for this SMTP server. Most SMTP servers require this.

data.name: smoothLabel2.HelpText
data.value: Specify your username for this SMTP server. Most SMTP servers require this.

data.name: smoothLabel1.HelpText
data.value: Specify the network port used by your SMTP server. In most cases this port is 25 and should not be changed unless you know for certain that it differs.

data.name: smoothLabel3.HelpText
data.value: Specify the name of your Internet SMTP mail server here. In most cases this is similar in form to mail.yourdomain.com or smtp.yourdomain.com.

data.name: header1.Description
data.value: Manage your SMTP Email Server settings.

data.name: lblRemoteManagement.HelpText
data.value: Check this if you want to allow this CallButler service to be managed from remote computers. If this is not checked, CallButler will only allow this instance of CallButler to managed from the same computer it is installed on.

data.name: smoothLabel13.HelpText
data.value: Specify a password here if you would like to require that a password be entered before allowing a user to connect to and manage this CallButler service.
